  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Hurdy-gurdy coups de poignet — the wrist snap technique that lifts the chien from the soundboard. Threshold sits at 0.25: the buzz bridge activates readily on any note played with intention. The four-stage buzz pipeline (BPF extraction, quadratic gate, cubic soft-clip, rattle BPF) is fully engaged. Drone strings at a fifth and octave below create the ancient drone bed. Mod wheel builds additional wheel pressure. This is the engine's most distinctive sound, made accessible: play quietly for clean drone, dig in for the rattle.",
